subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is similar to 
Heterospilus nigricoxus
but differs in having the stigma entirely brown (bicolored in 
Heterospilus nigricoxus
), the legs entirely yellow (hind coxa and femur brown in 
Heterospilus nigricoxus
), and granulate mesoscutal lobes without being rugose along notauli (as in 
Heterospilus nigricoxus
).
